At the 2010 [[census]],<ref name="GR2" /> there were 187 people, 77 households and 51 families residing in the CDP. The [[population density]] was {{convert|98.4|/sqmi}}. There were 111 housing units at an average density of {{convert|58.4|/sqmi}}. The racial make-up of the CDP was 97.9% White, 0.5% Asian, 0.5% Pacific Islander, 0.5% some other race and 0.5% two or more races.

There were 77 households, of which 31.2% had children under the age of 18 living with them, 48.1% were [[Marriage|married couples]] living together and 33.8% were non-families. 27.3% of all households were made up of individuals and 22.1% had someone living alone who was 65 years of age or older. The average household size was 2.43 and the average family size was 2.86. The median age was 41.2 years. Females made up 48.1% of the population and males 51.9%.

